I"Í<p>Wakeup from deep sleep with various options to turn on / off the radio.</p>

<p>In ESP8266, there are four options and params:</p>

<ol>
  <li>[<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">WAKE_RF_DEFAULT</code>] <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">deepsleepsetoption(0)</code>: Radio calibration after deep-sleep wake up depends on init data byte 108.</li>
  <li>[<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">WAKE_RFCAL</code>] <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">deepsleepsetoption(1)</code>: Radio calibration is done after deep-sleep wake up; this increases the current consumption.</li>
  <li>[<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">WAKE_NO_RFCAL</code>] <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">deepsleepsetoption(2)</code>: No radio calibration after deep-sleep wake up; this reduces the current consumption.</li>
  <li>[<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">WAKE_RF_DISABLED</code>] <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">deepsleepsetoption(4)</code>: Disable RF after deep-sleep wake up, just like modem sleep; this has the least current consumption; the device is not able to transmit or receive data after wake up.</li>
</ol>
